When the water level  in our backyard increases, water enters our house THROUGH  the floor tiles.  When the rain stops and the water level outside reduces, the water flooding our house is reabsorbed through the tiles. After 3 days of steady rains, usually 10 cm of water enters through the floor tilesin the house. In Michaung, we had 24cm or more. Best of luck for this endeavor.

When there is frequent rainfall leading to water standing in our backyard,  then groundwater enters our house THROUGH the floor tiles.  It is usually 10 cm water level flooding the house.
